Interface DynamicAssignmentState

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Bean, com.guidewire.commons.entity.BundleProvider, java.lang.Comparable<Bean>, com.guidewire.pl.domain.assignment.gen.DynamicAssignmentStateStubI, Editable, IGosuObject, com.guidewire.commons.entity.Keyable, KeyableBean, LastAssignedUserContainerBase, com.guidewire.pl.domain.assignment.gen.LastAssignedUserContainerBaseStubI, Retireable, com.guidewire.commons.entity.Sourceable, Versionable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DynamicAssignmentStateCoreExt

    public interface DynamicAssignmentState
extends com.guidewire.pl.domain.assignment.gen.DynamicAssignmentStateStubI
    DynamicAssignmentStateBase Maintains round-robin assignment state for a particular fingerprint. The fingerprint is generated from some entity (such as a UserSearchCriteria) which determines the set of users to be chosen via round-robin. This is an internal class which should only be used by the internals of the assignment engine.
